For Derived PIV Credentials issued at LOA-3, an issuer may implement all the requirements
necessary to issue these credentials remotely. In such a case, the issuer may not need to have an
issuing facility and issuing facility-specific controls may not be applicable. Regardless of the
system and process architecture on how PIV Card and Derived PIV Credentials are issued, it is
the responsibility of issuer organization to ensure that all applicable controls are implemented.




